285  //**Constructor*********************************************************************************
291  explicit inline TDMatTDMatMultExpr( const MT1& lhs, const MT2& rhs ) noexcept
292  : lhs_( lhs ) // Left-hand side dense matrix of the multiplication expression
293  , rhs_( rhs ) // Right-hand side dense matrix of the multiplication expression
294  {
295  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( lhs.columns() == rhs.rows(), "Invalid matrix sizes" );
296  }
297  //**********************************************************************************************
298 
299  //**Access operator*****************************************************************************
306  inline ReturnType operator()( size_t i, size_t j ) const {
307  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( i < lhs_.rows() , "Invalid row access index" );
308  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( j < rhs_.columns(), "Invalid column access index" );
309 
310  if( IsDiagonal<MT1>::value ) {
311  return lhs_(i,i) * rhs_(i,j);
312  }
313  else if( IsDiagonal<MT2>::value ) {
314  return lhs_(i,j) * rhs_(j,j);
315  }
316  else if( IsTriangular<MT1>::value || IsTriangular<MT2>::value ) {
317  const size_t begin( ( IsUpper<MT1>::value )
318  ?( ( IsLower<MT2>::value )
319  ?( max( ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT1>::value ? i+1UL : i )
320  , ( IsStrictlyLower<MT2>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
321  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT1>::value ? i+1UL : i ) )
322  :( ( IsLower<MT2>::value )
323  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT2>::value ? j+1UL : j )
324  :( 0UL ) ) );
325  const size_t end( ( IsLower<MT1>::value )
326  ?( ( IsUpper<MT2>::value )
327  ?( min( ( IsStrictlyLower<MT1>::value ? i : i+1UL )
328  , ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT2>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
329  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT1>::value ? i : i+1UL ) )
330  :( ( IsUpper<MT2>::value )
331  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT2>::value ? j : j+1UL )
332  :( lhs_.columns() ) ) );
333 
334  if( begin >= end ) return ElementType();
335 
336  const size_t n( end - begin );
337 
338  return subvector( row( lhs_, i ), begin, n ) * subvector( column( rhs_, j ), begin, n );
339  }
340  else {
341  return row( lhs_, i ) * column( rhs_, j );
342  }
343  }
344  //**********************************************************************************************
345 
346  //**At function*********************************************************************************
354  inline ReturnType at( size_t i, size_t j ) const {
355  if( i >= lhs_.rows() ) {
356  BLAZE_THROW_OUT_OF_RANGE( "Invalid row access index" );
357  }
358  if( j >= rhs_.columns() ) {
359  BLAZE_THROW_OUT_OF_RANGE( "Invalid column access index" );
360  }
361  return (*this)(i,j);
362  }
363  //**********************************************************************************************
364 
365  //**Rows function*******************************************************************************
370  inline size_t rows() const noexcept {
371  return lhs_.rows();
372  }
373  //**********************************************************************************************
374 
375  //**Columns function****************************************************************************
380  inline size_t columns() const noexcept {
381  return rhs_.columns();
382  }
383  //**********************************************************************************************
384 
385  //**Left operand access*************************************************************************
390  inline LeftOperand leftOperand() const noexcept {
391  return lhs_;
392  }
393  //**********************************************************************************************
394 
395  //**Right operand access************************************************************************
400  inline RightOperand rightOperand() const noexcept {
401  return rhs_;
402  }

413  return ( lhs_.isAliased( alias ) || rhs_.isAliased( alias ) );
414  }

425  return ( lhs_.isAliased( alias ) || rhs_.isAliased( alias ) );
426  }

445  return ( !BLAZE_BLAS_IS_PARALLEL ||
446  ( rows() * columns() < TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) ) &&
447  ( rows() * columns() >= SMP_TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD );
448  }

457  //**Assignment to dense matrices****************************************************************
470  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
471  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
472  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
473  assign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
474  {
475  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
476 
477  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
478  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
479 
480  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
481  return;
482  }
483  else if( rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
484  reset( ~lhs );
485  return;
486  }
487 
488  LT A( serial( rhs.lhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
489  RT B( serial( rhs.rhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
490 
491  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
492  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
493  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
494  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
495  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
496  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
497 
498  TDMatTDMatMultExpr::selectAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B );
499  }

503  //**Assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************************
514  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
515  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
516  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
517  static inline void selectAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
518  {
519  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value ) ||
520  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
521  selectSmallAssignKernel( C, A, B );
522  else
523  selectBlasAssignKernel( C, A, B );
524  }
526  //**********************************************************************************************
527 
528  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (general/general)**************************************
542  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
543  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
544  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
545  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
546  selectDefaultAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
547  {
548  const size_t M( A.rows() );
549  const size_t N( B.columns() );
550  const size_t K( A.columns() );
551 
552  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
553  {
554  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
555  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
556  :( 0UL ) );
557  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
558  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
559  :( K ) );
560  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin <= kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
561 
562  if( IsStrictlyTriangular<MT5>::value && kbegin == kend ) {
563  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
564  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
565  }
566  continue;
567  }
568 
569  {
570  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
571  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? kbegin+1UL : kbegin )
572  :( 0UL ) );
573  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
574  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? kbegin : kbegin+1UL )
575  :( M ) );
576  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
577 
578  if( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value ) {
579  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
580  reset( C(i,j) );
581  }
582  }
583  else if( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ) {
584  reset( C(0UL,j) );
585  }
586  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
587  C(i,j) = A(i,kbegin) * B(kbegin,j);
588  }
589  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value ) {
590  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
591  reset( C(i,j) );
592  }
593  }
594  else if( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ) {
595  reset( C(M-1UL,j) );
596  }
597  }
598 
599  for( size_t k=kbegin+1UL; k<kend; ++k )
600  {
601  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
602  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? k+1UL : k )
603  :( 0UL ) );
604  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
605  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? k-1UL : k )
606  :( M ) );
607  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
608 
609  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
610  C(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
611  }
612  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
613  C(iend,j) = A(iend,k) * B(k,j);
614  }
615  }
616  }
617  }
619  //**********************************************************************************************

621  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (general/diagonal)*************************************
635  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
636  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
637  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
638  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
639  selectDefaultAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
640  {
641  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
642 
643  const size_t M( A.rows() );
644  const size_t N( B.columns() );
645 
646  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
647  {
648  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
649  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j )
650  :( 0UL ) );
651  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
652  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL )
653  :( M ) );
654  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
655 
656  if( IsLower<MT4>::value ) {
657  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
658  reset( C(i,j) );
659  }
660  }
661  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
662  C(i,j) = A(i,j) * B(j,j);
663  }
664  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
665  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
666  reset( C(i,j) );
667  }
668  }
669  }
670  }
672  //**********************************************************************************************
673 
674  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/general)*************************************
688  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
689  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
690  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
691  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
692  selectDefaultAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
693  {
694  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
695 
696  const size_t M( A.rows() );
697  const size_t N( B.columns() );
698 
699  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
700  {
701  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
702  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
703  :( 0UL ) );
704  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
705  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
706  :( M ) );
707  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
708 
709  if( IsLower<MT4>::value ) {
710  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
711  reset( C(i,j) );
712  }
713  }
714  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
715  C(i,j) = A(i,i) * B(i,j);
716  }
717  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
718  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
719  reset( C(i,j) );
720  }
721  }
722  }
723  }

727  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)************************************
741  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
742  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
743  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
744  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
745  selectDefaultAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
746  {
747  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
748 
749  reset( C );
750 
751  for( size_t i=0UL; i<A.rows(); ++i ) {
752  C(i,i) = A(i,i) * B(i,i);
753  }
754  }
756  //**********************************************************************************************
757 
758  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (small matrices)***************************************
772  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
773  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
774  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
775  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
776  selectSmallAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
777  {
778  selectDefaultAssignKernel( C, A, B );
779  }
781  //**********************************************************************************************
782 
783  //**Vectorized default assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)******************
798  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
799  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
800  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
801  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
802  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
803  {
804  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT4 );
805  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT5 );
806  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT4> );
807  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT5> );
808 
809  if( IsResizable<MT4>::value && !IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
810  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
811  assign( ~C, A * tmp );
812  }
813  else if( !IsResizable<MT4>::value && IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
814  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
815  assign( ~C, tmp * B );
816  }
817  else if( B.rows() * B.columns() <= A.rows() * A.columns() ) {
818  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
819  assign( ~C, A * tmp );
820  }
821  else {
822  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
823  assign( ~C, tmp * B );
824  }
825  }
827  //**********************************************************************************************
828 
829  //**Vectorized default assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)***************
844  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
845  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
846  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
847  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
848  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
849  {
850  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT3>::value || !IsPadded<MT4>::value );
851 
852  const size_t M( A.rows() );
853  const size_t N( B.columns() );
854  const size_t K( A.columns() );
855 
856  const size_t ipos( remainder ? ( M & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : M );
857  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( M - ( M % SIMDSIZE ) ) == ipos, "Invalid end calculation" );
858 
859  size_t i( 0UL );
860 
861  if( IsIntegral_<ElementType> )
862  {
863  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*7UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*8UL ) {
864  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
865  {
866  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
867  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
868  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
869  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
870  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
871  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
872  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
873  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
874  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) )
875  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K ) : K ) );
876 
877  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
878 
879  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
880  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
881  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
882  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
883  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
884  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
885  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
886  xmm6 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,k) * b1;
887  xmm7 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,k) * b1;
888  xmm8 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,k) * b1;
889  }
890 
891  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 );
892  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
893  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );
894  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 );
895  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, xmm5 );
896  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, j, xmm6 );
897  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*6UL, j, xmm7 );
898  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*7UL, j, xmm8 );
899  }
900  }
901  }
902 
903  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*4UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*5UL )
904  {
905  size_t j( 0UL );
906 
907  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
908  {
909  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
910  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
911  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
912  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
913  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
914  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
915  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
916  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
917  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
918  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) : K ) );
919 
920  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8, xmm9, xmm10;
921 
922  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
923  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
924  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
925  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
926  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
927  const SIMDType a5( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) );
928  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
929  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
930  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
931  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
932  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
933  xmm4 += a4 * b1;
934  xmm5 += a5 * b1;
935  xmm6 += a1 * b2;
936  xmm7 += a2 * b2;
937  xmm8 += a3 * b2;
938  xmm9 += a4 * b2;
939  xmm10 += a5 * b2;
940  }
941 
942  (~C).store( i , j , xmm1 );
943  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , xmm2 );
944  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , xmm3 );
945  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j , xmm4 );
946  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j , xmm5 );
947  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, xmm6 );
948  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, xmm7 );
949  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, xmm8 );
950  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j+1UL, xmm9 );
951  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j+1UL, xmm10 );
952  }
953 
954  if( j < N )
955  {
956  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
957  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
958  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
959  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
960  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
961  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) ):( K ) );
962 
963  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5;
964 
965  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
966  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
967  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
968  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
969  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
970  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
971  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
972  }
973 
974  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 );
975  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
976  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );
977  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 );
978  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, xmm5 );
979  }
980  }
981 
982  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*3UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*4UL )
983  {
984  size_t j( 0UL );
985 
986  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
987  {
988  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
989  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
990  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
991  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
992  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
993  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
994  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
995  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
996  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
997  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K ) : K ) );
998 
999  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
1000 
1001  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1002  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1003  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
1004  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
1005  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
1006  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
1007  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
1008  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1009  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
1010  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
1011  xmm4 += a4 * b1;
1012  xmm5 += a1 * b2;
1013  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
1014  xmm7 += a3 * b2;
1015  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
1016  }
1017 
1018  (~C).store( i , j , xmm1 );
1019  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , xmm2 );
1020  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , xmm3 );
1021  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j , xmm4 );
1022  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, xmm5 );
1023  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, xmm6 );
1024  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, xmm7 );
1025  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j+1UL, xmm8 );
1026  }
1027 
1028  if( j < N )
1029  {
1030  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1031  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1032  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1033  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1034  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1035  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K ) ):( K ) );
1036 
1037  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
1038 
1039  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1040  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
1041  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
1042  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
1043  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
1044  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
1045  }
1046 
1047  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 );
1048  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
1049  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );
1050  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 );
1051  }
1052  }
1053 
1054  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*2UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*3UL )
1055  {
1056  size_t j( 0UL );
1057 
1058  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
1059  {
1060  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1061  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1062  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1063  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1064  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1065  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1066  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1067  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
1068  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
1069  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, K ) : K ) );
1070 
1071  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6;
1072 
1073  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1074  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1075  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
1076  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
1077  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
1078  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
1079  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1080  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
1081  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
1082  xmm4 += a1 * b2;
1083  xmm5 += a2 * b2;
1084  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
1085  }
1086 
1087  (~C).store( i , j , xmm1 );
1088  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , xmm2 );
1089  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , xmm3 );
1090  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, xmm4 );
1091  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, xmm5 );
1092  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, xmm6 );
1093  }
1094 
1095  if( j < N )
1096  {
1097  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1098  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1099  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1100  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1101  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1102  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, K ) ):( K ) );
1103 
1104  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3;
1105 
1106  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1107  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
1108  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
1109  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
1110  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
1111  }
1112 
1113  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 );
1114  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
1115  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );
1116  }
1117  }
1118 
1119  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*2UL )
1120  {
1121  size_t j( 0UL );
1122 
1123  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
1124  {
1125  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1126  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1127  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1128  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1129  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1130  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1131  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1132  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
1133  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
1134  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, K ) : K ) );
1135 
1136  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
1137 
1138  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1139  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1140  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE,k) );
1141  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
1142  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
1143  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1144  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
1145  xmm3 += a1 * b2;
1146  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
1147  }
1148 
1149  (~C).store( i , j , xmm1 );
1150  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE, j , xmm2 );
1151  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, xmm3 );
1152  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE, j+1UL, xmm4 );
1153  }
1154 
1155  if( j < N )
1156  {
1157  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1158  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1159  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1160  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1161  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1162  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, K ) ):( K ) );
1163 
1164  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
1165 
1166  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1167  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
1168  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
1169  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE,k) * b1;
1170  }
1171 
1172  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 );
1173  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE, j, xmm2 );
1174  }
1175  }
1176 
1177  for( ; i<ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE )
1178  {
1179  size_t j( 0UL );
1180 
1181  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
1182  {
1183  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1184  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1185  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1186  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1187  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1188  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1189  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL )
1190  :( K ) );
1191 
1192  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
1193 
1194  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1195  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
1196  xmm1 += a1 * set( B(k,j ) );
1197  xmm2 += a1 * set( B(k,j+1UL) );
1198  }
1199 
1200  (~C).store( i, j , xmm1 );
1201  (~C).store( i, j+1UL, xmm2 );
1202  }
1203 
1204  if( j < N )
1205  {
1206  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1207  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1208  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1209  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1210  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1211 
1212  SIMDType xmm1;
1213 
1214  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<K; ++k ) {
1215  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * set( B(k,j) );
1216  }
1217 
1218  (~C).store( i, j, xmm1 );
1219  }
1220  }
1221 
1222  for( ; remainder && i<M; ++i )
1223  {
1224  size_t j( 0UL );
1225 
1226  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
1227  {
1228  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1229  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1230  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1231  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1232  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1233  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1234  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL )
1235  :( K ) );
1236 
1237  ElementType value1 = ElementType();
1238  ElementType value2 = ElementType();
1239 
1240  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1241  value1 += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
1242  value2 += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
1243  }
1244 
1245  (~C)(i,j ) = value1;
1246  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = value2;
1247  }
1248 
1249  if( j < N )
1250  {
1251  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1252  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1253  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1254  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1255  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1256 
1257  ElementType value = ElementType();
1258 
1259  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<K; ++k ) {
1260  value += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
1261  }
1262 
1263  (~C)(i,j) = value;
1264  }
1265  }
1266  }
1268  //**********************************************************************************************
1269 
1270  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)***************************************
1284  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1285  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1286  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1287  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1288  selectLargeAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1289  {
1290  selectDefaultAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1291  }

1314  selectLargeAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1315  {
1316  mmm( C, A, B, ElementType(1), ElementType(0) );
1317  }

1345 
1346  //**BLAS-based assignment to dense matrices*****************************************************
1347 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
1348 
1361  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1362  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1363  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1364  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1365  selectBlasAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1366  {
1367  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
1368 
1369  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
1370  assign( C, B );
1371  trmm( C, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
1372  }
1373  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
1374  assign( C, A );
1375  trmm( C, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
1376  }
1377  else {
1378  gemm( C, A, B, ET(1), ET(0) );
1379  }
1380  }
1382 #endif

1385  //**Assignment to sparse matrices***************************************************************
1398  template< typename MT // Type of the target sparse matrix
1399  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target sparse matrix
1400  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
1401  assign( SparseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
1402  {
1403  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
1404 
1405  typedef IfTrue_< SO, ResultType, OppositeType > TmpType;
1406 
1407  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
1408  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
1409  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
1410  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
1411  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MATRICES_MUST_HAVE_SAME_STORAGE_ORDER( MT, TmpType );
1412  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_REFERENCE_TYPE( CompositeType_<TmpType> );
1413 
1414  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1415  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1416 
1417  const TmpType tmp( serial( rhs ) );
1418  assign( ~lhs, tmp );
1419  }
1421  //**********************************************************************************************
1422 
1423  //**Restructuring assignment to row-major matrices**********************************************
1438  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
1439  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
1440  assign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
1441  {
1442  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
1443 
1444  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
1445 
1446  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1447  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1448 
1449  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
1450  assign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
1451  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
1452  assign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * rhs.rhs_ );
1453  else
1454  assign( ~lhs, rhs.lhs_ * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
1455  }

1458 
1459  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices*******************************************************
1472  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
1473  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
1474  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
1475  addAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
1476  {
1477  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
1478 
1479  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1480  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1481 
1482  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
1483  return;
1484  }
1485 
1486  LT A( serial( rhs.lhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
1487  RT B( serial( rhs.rhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
1488 
1489  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1490  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1491  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1492  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
1493  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
1494  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
1495 
1496  TDMatTDMatMultExpr::selectAddAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B );
1497  }
1499  //**********************************************************************************************
1500 
1501  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)************************************
1512  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1513  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1514  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1515  static inline void selectAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1516  {
1517  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value ) ||
1518  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
1519  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1520  else
1521  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1522  }
1524  //**********************************************************************************************
1525 
1526  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (general/general)*****************************
1540  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1541  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1542  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1543  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
1544  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1545  {
1546  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1547  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1548  const size_t K( A.columns() );
1549 
1550  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
1551  {
1552  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1553  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
1554  :( 0UL ) );
1555  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1556  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
1557  :( K ) );
1558  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin <= kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1559 
1560  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k )
1561  {
1562  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1563  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? k+1UL : k )
1564  :( 0UL ) );
1565  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1566  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? k : k+1UL )
1567  :( M ) );
1568  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1569 
1570  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
1571  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
1572 
1573  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
1574  C(i ,j) += A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
1575  C(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
1576  }
1577  if( ipos < iend ) {
1578  C(ipos,j) += A(ipos,k) * B(k,j);
1579  }
1580  }
1581  }
1582  }
1584  //**********************************************************************************************
1585 
1586  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (general/diagonal)****************************
1600  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1601  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1602  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1603  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
1604  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1605  {
1606  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
1607 
1608  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1609  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1610 
1611  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
1612  {
1613  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1614  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j )
1615  :( 0UL ) );
1616  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1617  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL )
1618  :( M ) );
1619  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1620 
1621  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
1622  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
1623 
1624  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
1625  C(i ,j) += A(i ,j) * B(j,j);
1626  C(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,j) * B(j,j);
1627  }
1628  if( ipos < iend ) {
1629  C(ipos,j) += A(ipos,j) * B(j,j);
1630  }
1631  }
1632  }
1634  //**********************************************************************************************
1635 
1636  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/general)****************************
1650  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1651  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1652  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1653  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
1654  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1655  {
1656  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
1657 
1658  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1659  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1660 
1661  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
1662  {
1663  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1664  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
1665  :( 0UL ) );
1666  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1667  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
1668  :( M ) );
1669  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
1670 
1671  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
1672  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
1673 
1674  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
1675  C(i ,j) += A(i ,i ) * B(i ,j);
1676  C(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,i+1UL) * B(i+1UL,j);
1677  }
1678  if( ipos < iend ) {
1679  C(ipos,j) += A(ipos,ipos) * B(ipos,j);
1680  }
1681  }
1682  }
1684  //**********************************************************************************************
1685 
1686  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)***************************
1700  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1701  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1702  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1703  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
1704  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1705  {
1706  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
1707 
1708  for( size_t i=0UL; i<A.rows(); ++i ) {
1709  C(i,i) += A(i,i) * B(i,i);
1710  }
1711  }

1714 
1715  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (small matrices)******************************
1729  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1730  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1731  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1732  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1733  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1734  {
1735  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( C, A, B );
1736  }
1738  //**********************************************************************************************
1739 
1740  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)*********
1755  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1756  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1757  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1758  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1759  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1760  {
1761  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT4 );
1762  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT5 );
1763  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT4> );
1764  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT5> );
1765 
1766  if( IsResizable<MT4>::value && !IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
1767  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
1768  addAssign( ~C, A * tmp );
1769  }
1770  else if( !IsResizable<MT4>::value && IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
1771  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
1772  addAssign( ~C, tmp * B );
1773  }
1774  else if( B.rows() * B.columns() <= A.rows() * A.columns() ) {
1775  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
1776  addAssign( ~C, A * tmp );
1777  }
1778  else {
1779  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
1780  addAssign( ~C, tmp * B );
1781  }
1782  }
1784  //**********************************************************************************************
1785 
1786  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)******
1801  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
1802  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
1803  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
1804  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
1805  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
1806  {
1807  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT3>::value || !IsPadded<MT4>::value );
1808 
1809  const size_t M( A.rows() );
1810  const size_t N( B.columns() );
1811  const size_t K( A.columns() );
1812 
1813  const size_t ipos( remainder ? ( M & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : M );
1814  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( M - ( M % SIMDSIZE ) ) == ipos, "Invalid end calculation" );
1815 
1816  size_t i( 0UL );
1817 
1818  if( IsIntegral_<ElementType> )
1819  {
1820  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*7UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*8UL ) {
1821  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
1822  {
1823  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1824  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1825  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1826  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1827  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1828  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1829  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1830  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
1831  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) )
1832  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K ) : K ) );
1833 
1834  SIMDType xmm1( (~C).load(i ,j) );
1835  SIMDType xmm2( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) );
1836  SIMDType xmm3( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) );
1837  SIMDType xmm4( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) );
1838  SIMDType xmm5( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j) );
1839  SIMDType xmm6( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,j) );
1840  SIMDType xmm7( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,j) );
1841  SIMDType xmm8( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,j) );
1842 
1843  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1844  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
1845  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
1846  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
1847  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
1848  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
1849  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
1850  xmm6 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,k) * b1;
1851  xmm7 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,k) * b1;
1852  xmm8 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,k) * b1;
1853  }
1854 
1855  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 );
1856  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
1857  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );
1858  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 );
1859  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, xmm5 );
1860  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, j, xmm6 );
1861  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*6UL, j, xmm7 );
1862  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*7UL, j, xmm8 );
1863  }
1864  }
1865  }
1866 
1867  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*4UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*5UL )
1868  {
1869  size_t j( 0UL );
1870 
1871  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
1872  {
1873  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
1874  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
1875  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
1876  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
1877  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
1878  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
1879  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
1880  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
1881  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
1882  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) : K ) );
1883 
1884  SIMDType xmm1 ( (~C).load(i ,j ) );
1885  SIMDType xmm2 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j ) );
1886  SIMDType xmm3 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j ) );
1887  SIMDType xmm4 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j ) );
1888  SIMDType xmm5 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j ) );
1889  SIMDType xmm6 ( (~C).load(i ,j+1UL) );
1890  SIMDType xmm7 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j+1UL) );
1891  SIMDType xmm8 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j+1UL) );
1892  SIMDType xmm9 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j+1UL) );
1893  SIMDType xmm10( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j+1UL) );
1894 
1895  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
1896  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
1897  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
1898  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
1899  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
1900  const SIMDType a5( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) );
1901  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
1902  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
1903  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
1904  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
1905  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
1906  xmm4 += a4 * b1;
1907  xmm5 += a5 * b1;
1908  xmm6 += a1 * b2;
1909  xmm7 += a2 * b2;
1910  xmm8 += a3 * b2;
1911  xmm9 += a4 * b2;
1912  xmm10 += a5 * b2;
1913  }

1919  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j , xmm5 );

2231  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );

2233  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL )
2234  :( K ) );
2235 
2236  ElementType value1( (~C)(i,j ) );
2237  ElementType value2( (~C)(i,j+1UL) );
2238 
2239  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
2240  value1 += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
2241  value2 += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);

2345  //**BLAS-based addition assignment to dense matrices********************************************
2346 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
2347 
2360  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2361  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2362  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2363  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2364  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2365  {
2366  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
2367 
2368  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
2369  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
2370  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
2371  addAssign( C, tmp );
2372  }
2373  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
2374  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
2375  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
2376  addAssign( C, tmp );
2377  }
2378  else {
2379  gemm( C, A, B, ET(1), ET(1) );
2380  }
2381  }
2383 #endif

2386  //**Restructuring addition assignment to row-major matrices*************************************
2401  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
2402  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
2403  addAssign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
2404  {
2405  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
2406 
2407  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
2408 
2409  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2410  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
2411 
2412  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
2413  addAssign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
2414  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
2415  addAssign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * rhs.rhs_ );
2416  else
2417  addAssign( ~lhs, rhs.lhs_ * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
2418  }
2420  //**********************************************************************************************
2421 
2422  //**Addition assignment to sparse matrices******************************************************
2423  // No special implementation for the addition assignment to sparse matrices.
2424  //**********************************************************************************************
2425 
2426  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices****************************************************
2439  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
2440  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
2441  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
2442  subAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
2443  {
2444  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
2445 
2446  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2447  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
2448 
2449  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
2450  return;
2451  }
2452 
2453  LT A( serial( rhs.lhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
2454  RT B( serial( rhs.rhs_ ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
2455 
2456  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2457  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
2458  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2459  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
2460  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
2461  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
2462 
2463  TDMatTDMatMultExpr::selectSubAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B );
2464  }
2466  //**********************************************************************************************
2467 
2468  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************
2479  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2480  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2481  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2482  static inline void selectSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2483  {
2484  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value ) ||
2485  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
2486  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( C, A, B );
2487  else
2488  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( C, A, B );
2489  }
2491  //**********************************************************************************************
2492 
2493  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (general/general)**************************
2507  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2508  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2509  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2510  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
2511  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2512  {
2513  const size_t M( A.rows() );
2514  const size_t N( B.columns() );
2515  const size_t K( A.columns() );
2516 
2517  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
2518  {
2519  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2520  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
2521  :( 0UL ) );
2522  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
2523  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
2524  :( K ) );
2525  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin <= kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
2526 
2527  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k )
2528  {
2529  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2530  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? k+1UL : k )
2531  :( 0UL ) );
2532  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2533  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? k : k+1UL )
2534  :( M ) );
2535  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
2536 
2537  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
2538  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
2539 
2540  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
2541  C(i ,j) -= A(i ,k) * B(k,j);
2542  C(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,k) * B(k,j);
2543  }
2544  if( ipos < iend ) {
2545  C(ipos,j) -= A(ipos,k) * B(k,j);
2546  }
2547  }
2548  }
2549  }
2551  //**********************************************************************************************
2552 
2553  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (general/diagonal)*************************
2567  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2568  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2569  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2570  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
2571  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2572  {
2573  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
2574 
2575  const size_t M( A.rows() );
2576  const size_t N( B.columns() );
2577 
2578  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
2579  {
2580  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2581  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j )
2582  :( 0UL ) );
2583  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2584  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL )
2585  :( M ) );
2586  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
2587 
2588  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
2589  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
2590 
2591  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
2592  C(i ,j) -= A(i ,j) * B(j,j);
2593  C(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,j) * B(j,j);
2594  }
2595  if( ipos < iend ) {
2596  C(ipos,j) -= A(ipos,j) * B(j,j);
2597  }
2598  }
2599  }
2601  //**********************************************************************************************
2602 
2603  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/general)*************************
2617  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2618  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2619  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2620  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
2621  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2622  {
2623  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
2624 
2625  const size_t M( A.rows() );
2626  const size_t N( B.columns() );
2627 
2628  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
2629  {
2630  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2631  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
2632  :( 0UL ) );
2633  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
2634  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
2635  :( M ) );
2636  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
2637 
2638  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
2639  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
2640 
2641  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
2642  C(i ,j) -= A(i ,i ) * B(i ,j);
2643  C(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,i+1UL) * B(i+1UL,j);
2644  }
2645  if( ipos < iend ) {
2646  C(ipos,j) -= A(ipos,ipos) * B(ipos,j);
2647  }
2648  }
2649  }

2653  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)************************
2667  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2668  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2669  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2670  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
2671  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2672  {
2673  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
2674 
2675  for( size_t i=0UL; i<A.rows(); ++i ) {
2676  C(i,i) -= A(i,i) * B(i,i);
2677  }
2678  }

2682  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (small matrices)***************************
2696  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2697  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2698  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2699  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2700  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2701  {
2702  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( C, A, B );
2703  }

2706 
2707  //**Vectorized default subtraction assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)******
2722  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2723  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2724  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2725  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2726  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2727  {
2728  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT4 );
2729  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT5 );
2730  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT4> );
2731  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT5> );
2732 
2733  if( IsResizable<MT4>::value && !IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
2734  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
2735  subAssign( ~C, A * tmp );
2736  }
2737  else if( !IsResizable<MT4>::value && IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
2738  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
2739  subAssign( ~C, tmp * B );
2740  }
2741  else if( B.rows() * B.columns() <= A.rows() * A.columns() ) {
2742  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
2743  subAssign( ~C, A * tmp );
2744  }
2745  else {
2746  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
2747  subAssign( ~C, tmp * B );
2748  }
2749  }
2751  //**********************************************************************************************
2752 
2753  //**Vectorized default subtraction assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)***
2768  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
2769  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
2770  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
2771  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
2772  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
2773  {
2774  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT3>::value || !IsPadded<MT4>::value );
2775 
2776  const size_t M( A.rows() );
2777  const size_t N( B.columns() );
2778  const size_t K( A.columns() );
2779 
2780  const size_t ipos( remainder ? ( M & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : M );
2781  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( M - ( M % SIMDSIZE ) ) == ipos, "Invalid end calculation" );
2782 
2783  size_t i( 0UL );
2784 
2785  if( IsIntegral_<ElementType> )
2786  {
2787  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*7UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*8UL ) {
2788  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
2789  {
2790  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2791  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2792  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
2793  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
2794  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
2795  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
2796  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2797  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
2798  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) )
2799  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K ) : K ) );
2800 
2801  SIMDType xmm1( (~C).load(i ,j) );
2802  SIMDType xmm2( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) );
2803  SIMDType xmm3( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) );
2804  SIMDType xmm4( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) );
2805  SIMDType xmm5( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j) );
2806  SIMDType xmm6( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,j) );
2807  SIMDType xmm7( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,j) );
2808  SIMDType xmm8( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,j) );
2809 
2810  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
2811  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
2812  xmm1 -= A.load(i ,k) * b1;
2813  xmm2 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
2814  xmm3 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
2815  xmm4 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
2816  xmm5 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
2817  xmm6 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,k) * b1;
2818  xmm7 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,k) * b1;
2819  xmm8 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,k) * b1;
2820  }
2821 
2822  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 );
2823  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
2824  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );
2825  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 );
2826  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, xmm5 );
2827  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, j, xmm6 );
2828  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*6UL, j, xmm7 );
2829  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*7UL, j, xmm8 );
2830  }
2831  }
2832  }
2833 
2834  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*4UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*5UL )
2835  {
2836  size_t j( 0UL );
2837 
2838  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
2839  {
2840  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2841  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2842  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
2843  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
2844  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
2845  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
2846  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2847  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
2848  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
2849  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) : K ) );
2850 
2851  SIMDType xmm1 ( (~C).load(i ,j ) );
2852  SIMDType xmm2 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j ) );
2853  SIMDType xmm3 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j ) );
2854  SIMDType xmm4 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j ) );
2855  SIMDType xmm5 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j ) );
2856  SIMDType xmm6 ( (~C).load(i ,j+1UL) );
2857  SIMDType xmm7 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j+1UL) );
2858  SIMDType xmm8 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j+1UL) );
2859  SIMDType xmm9 ( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j+1UL) );
2860  SIMDType xmm10( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j+1UL) );
2861 
2862  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
2863  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
2864  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
2865  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
2866  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
2867  const SIMDType a5( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) );
2868  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
2869  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
2870  xmm1 -= a1 * b1;
2871  xmm2 -= a2 * b1;
2872  xmm3 -= a3 * b1;
2873  xmm4 -= a4 * b1;
2874  xmm5 -= a5 * b1;
2875  xmm6 -= a1 * b2;
2876  xmm7 -= a2 * b2;
2877  xmm8 -= a3 * b2;
2878  xmm9 -= a4 * b2;
2879  xmm10 -= a5 * b2;
2880  }
2881 
2882  (~C).store( i , j , xmm1 );
2883  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , xmm2 );
2884  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , xmm3 );
2885  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j , xmm4 );
2886  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j , xmm5 );
2887  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, xmm6 );
2888  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, xmm7 );
2889  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, xmm8 );
2890  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j+1UL, xmm9 );
2891  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j+1UL, xmm10 );
2892  }
2893 
2894  if( j < N )
2895  {
2896  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2897  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2898  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
2899  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
2900  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
2901  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) ):( K ) );
2902 
2903  SIMDType xmm1( (~C).load(i ,j) );
2904  SIMDType xmm2( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) );
2905  SIMDType xmm3( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) );
2906  SIMDType xmm4( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) );
2907  SIMDType xmm5( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j) );
2908 
2909  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
2910  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
2911  xmm1 -= A.load(i ,k) * b1;
2912  xmm2 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
2913  xmm3 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
2914  xmm4 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
2915  xmm5 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
2916  }
2917

2919  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
2920  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );

2933  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2934  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
2935  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
2936  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );

2938  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
2939  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
2940  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
2941  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K ) : K ) );
2942 
2943  SIMDType xmm1( (~C).load(i ,j ) );
2944  SIMDType xmm2( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j ) );

2957  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );

2978 
2979  if( j < N )
2980  {
2981  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
2982  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
2983  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
2984  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
2985  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
2986  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K ) ):( K ) );
2987 
2988  SIMDType xmm1( (~C).load(i ,j) );
2989  SIMDType xmm2( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) );
2990  SIMDType xmm3( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) );
2991  SIMDType xmm4( (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) );
2992 
2993  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
2994  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
2995  xmm1 -= A.load(i ,k) * b1;
2996  xmm2 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
2997  xmm3 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
2998  xmm4 -= A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
2999  }
3000

3002  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 );
3003  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 );
3004  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 );
3005  }
3006  }

3015  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3016  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )

3018  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );

3020  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )

3022  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )

3035  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );

3043  xmm6 -= a3 * b2;

3050  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, xmm5 );

3106  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );

3150  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )

3155  :( K ) );

3163  xmm2 -= a1 * set( B(k,j+1UL) );
3164  }

3167  (~C).store( i, j+1UL, xmm2 );

3172  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
3173  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )

3175  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
3176  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );

3182  }

3193  {
3194  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
3195  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3196  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
3197  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
3198  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
3199  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
3200  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL )
3201  :( K ) );
3202 
3203  ElementType value1( (~C)(i,j ) );
3204  ElementType value2( (~C)(i,j+1UL) );
3205 
3206  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
3207  value1 -= A(i,k) * B(k,j );
3208  value2 -= A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
3209  }
3210 
3211  (~C)(i,j ) = value1;
3212  (~C)(i,j+1UL) = value2;
3213  }

3215  if( j < N )
3216  {
3217  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
3218  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
3219  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
3220  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
3221  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
3222 
3223  ElementType value( (~C)(i,j) );
3224 
3225  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<K; ++k ) {
3226  value -= A(i,k) * B(k,j);
3227  }
3228

3230  }

3313 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
3314 
3327  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
3328  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
3329  , typename MT5 > // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
3330  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5> >
3331  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B )
3332  {
3333  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
3334 
3335  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
3336  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
3337  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
3338  subAssign( C, tmp );
3339  }
3340  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
3341  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
3342  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(1) );
3343  subAssign( C, tmp );
3344  }
3345  else {
3346  gemm( C, A, B, ET(-1), ET(1) );
3347  }
3348  }

3353  //**Restructuring subtraction assignment to row-major matrices**********************************
3369  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
3370  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
3371  subAssign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
3372  {
3373  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
3374 
3375  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
3376 
3377  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3378  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3379 
3380  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
3381  subAssign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
3382  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
3383  subAssign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * rhs.rhs_ );
3384  else
3385  subAssign( ~lhs, rhs.lhs_ * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
3386  }

3402  //**SMP assignment to dense matrices************************************************************
3418  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
3419  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
3420  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
3421  smpAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
3422  {
3423  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
3424 
3425  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3426  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3427 
3428  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
3429  return;
3430  }
3431  else if( rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
3432  reset( ~lhs );
3433  return;
3434  }
3435 
3436  LT A( rhs.lhs_ ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
3437  RT B( rhs.rhs_ ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
3438 
3439  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3440  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3441  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3442  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3443  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3444  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
3445 
3446  smpAssign( ~lhs, A * B );
3447  }

3467  template< typename MT // Type of the target sparse matrix
3468  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target sparse matrix

3470  smpAssign( SparseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
3471  {

3473

3475

3479  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
3480  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MATRICES_MUST_HAVE_SAME_STORAGE_ORDER( MT, TmpType );
3481  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_REFERENCE_TYPE( CompositeType_<TmpType> );
3482 
3483  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3484  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3485 
3486  const TmpType tmp( rhs );
3487  smpAssign( ~lhs, tmp );
3488  }

3633  smpSubAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
3634  {
3635  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
3636 
3637  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3638  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3639 
3640  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || rhs.lhs_.columns() == 0UL ) {
3641  return;
3642  }
3643 
3644  LT A( rhs.lhs_ ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
3645  RT B( rhs.rhs_ ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
3646 
3647  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == rhs.lhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3648  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == rhs.lhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3649  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == rhs.rhs_.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3650  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == rhs.rhs_.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3651  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3652  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
3653 
3654  smpSubAssign( ~lhs, A * B );
3655  }
3657  //**********************************************************************************************
3658 
3659  //**Restructuring SMP subtraction assignment to row-major matrices******************************
3675  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
3676  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
3677  smpSubAssign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const TDMatTDMatMultExpr& rhs )
3678  {
3679  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
3680 
3681  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
3682 
3683  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
3684  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
3685 
3686  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
3687  smpSubAssign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
3688  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
3689  smpSubAssign( ~lhs, trans( rhs.lhs_ ) * rhs.rhs_ );
3690  else
3691  smpSubAssign( ~lhs, rhs.lhs_ * trans( rhs.rhs_ ) );
3692  }
3694  //**********************************************************************************************
3695 
3696  //**SMP subtraction assignment to sparse matrices***********************************************
3697  // No special implementation for the SMP subtraction assignment to sparse matrices.
3698  //**********************************************************************************************
3699 
3700  //**SMP multiplication assignment to dense matrices*********************************************
3701  // No special implementation for the SMP multiplication assignment to dense matrices.
3702  //**********************************************************************************************
3703 
3704  //**SMP multiplication assignment to sparse matrices********************************************
3705  // No special implementation for the SMP multiplication assignment to sparse matrices.
3706  //**********************************************************************************************
3707 
3708  //**Compile time checks*************************************************************************
3710  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MT1 );
3711  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT1 );
3712  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MT2 );
3713  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT2 );
3714  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_FORM_VALID_MATMATMULTEXPR( MT1, MT2 );
3716  //**********************************************************************************************
3717 };

4011  //**Assignment to dense matrices****************************************************************
4023  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
4024  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
4025  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
4026  assign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
4027  {
4028  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
4029 
4030  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4031  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4032 
4033  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
4034  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
4035 
4036  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
4037  return;
4038  }
4039  else if( left.columns() == 0UL ) {
4040  reset( ~lhs );
4041  return;
4042  }
4043 
4044  LT A( serial( left ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
4045  RT B( serial( right ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
4046 
4047  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4048  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
4049  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4050  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
4051  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4052  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4053 
4054  DMatScalarMultExpr::selectAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B, rhs.scalar_ );
4055  }

4058  //**Assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************************
4069  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4070  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4071  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4072  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4073  static inline void selectAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4074  {
4075  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value ) ||
4076  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
4077  selectSmallAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
4078  else
4079  selectBlasAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
4080  }
