4082 
4083  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (general/general)**************************************
4097  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4098  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4099  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4100  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4101  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
4102  selectDefaultAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4103  {
4104  const size_t M( A.rows() );
4105  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4106  const size_t K( A.columns() );
4107 
4108  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
4109  {
4110  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4111  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
4112  :( 0UL ) );
4113  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4114  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
4115  :( K ) );
4116  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( kbegin <= kend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4117 
4118  if( IsStrictlyTriangular<MT5>::value && kbegin == kend ) {
4119  for( size_t i=0UL; i<M; ++i ) {
4120  reset( (~C)(i,j) );
4121  }
4122  continue;
4123  }
4124 
4125  {
4126  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4127  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? kbegin+1UL : kbegin )
4128  :( 0UL ) );
4129  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4130  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? kbegin : kbegin+1UL )
4131  :( M ) );
4132  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4133 
4134  if( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value ) {
4135  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
4136  reset( C(i,j) );
4137  }
4138  }
4139  else if( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ) {
4140  reset( C(0UL,j) );
4141  }
4142  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
4143  C(i,j) = A(i,kbegin) * B(kbegin,j);
4144  }
4145  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value ) {
4146  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
4147  reset( C(i,j) );
4148  }
4149  }
4150  else if( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ) {
4151  reset( C(M-1UL,j) );
4152  }
4153  }
4154 
4155  for( size_t k=kbegin+1UL; k<kend; ++k )
4156  {
4157  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4158  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? k+1UL : k )
4159  :( 0UL ) );
4160  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4161  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? k-1UL : k )
4162  :( M ) );
4163  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4164 
4165  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
4166  C(i,j) += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
4167  }
4168  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
4169  C(iend,j) = A(iend,k) * B(k,j);
4170  }
4171  }
4172 
4173  {
4174  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value && IsLower<MT5>::value )
4175  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value || IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
4176  :( 0UL ) );
4177  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value && IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4178  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value || IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
4179  :( M ) );
4180  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4181 
4182  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
4183  C(i,j) *= scalar;
4184  }
4185  }
4186  }
4187  }
4188  //**********************************************************************************************
4189 
4190  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (general/diagonal)*************************************
4204  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4205  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4206  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4207  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4208  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
4209  selectDefaultAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4210  {
4211  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
4212 
4213  const size_t M( A.rows() );
4214  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4215 
4216  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
4217  {
4218  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4219  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j )
4220  :( 0UL ) );
4221  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4222  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL )
4223  :( M ) );
4224  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
4225 
4226  if( IsLower<MT4>::value ) {
4227  for( size_t i=0UL; i<ibegin; ++i ) {
4228  reset( C(i,j) );
4229  }
4230  }
4231  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<iend; ++i ) {
4232  C(i,j) = A(i,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
4233  }
4234  if( IsUpper<MT4>::value ) {
4235  for( size_t i=iend; i<M; ++i ) {
4236  reset( C(i,j) );
4237  }
4238  }
4239  }
4240  }

4260  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value

4272  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
4273  :( 0UL ) );

4275  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
4276  :( M ) );

4289  reset( C(i,j) );
4290  }
4291  }
4292  }

4296  //**Default assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)************************************
4310  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix

4352  //**Vectorized default assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)******************
4367  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix

4369  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4370  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4371  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
4372  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4373  {
4374  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT4 );
4375  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT5 );
4376  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT4> );
4377  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT5> );
4378 
4379  if( IsResizable<MT4>::value && !IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
4380  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
4381  assign( ~C, A * tmp * scalar );
4382  }
4383  else if( !IsResizable<MT4>::value && IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
4384  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
4385  assign( ~C, tmp * B * scalar );
4386  }
4387  else if( B.rows() * B.columns() <= A.rows() * A.columns() ) {
4388  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
4389  assign( ~C, A * tmp * scalar );
4390  }
4391  else {
4392  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
4393  assign( ~C, tmp * B * scalar );
4394  }
4395  }
4396  //**********************************************************************************************
4397 
4398  //**Vectorized default assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)***************
4413  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4414  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4415  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4416  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4417  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
4418  selectSmallAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4419  {
4420  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT3>::value || !IsPadded<MT4>::value );
4421 
4422  const size_t M( A.rows() );
4423  const size_t N( B.columns() );
4424  const size_t K( A.columns() );
4425 
4426  const size_t ipos( remainder ? ( M & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : M );
4427  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( M - ( M % SIMDSIZE ) ) == ipos, "Invalid end calculation" );
4428 
4429  const SIMDType factor( set( scalar ) );
4430 
4431  size_t i( 0UL );
4432 
4433  if( IsIntegral_<ElementType> )
4434  {
4435  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*7UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*8UL ) {
4436  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
4437  {
4438  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4439  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4440  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
4441  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
4442  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
4443  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4444  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4445  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
4446  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) )
4447  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K ) : K ) );
4448 
4449  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
4450 
4451  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
4452  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
4453  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
4454  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
4455  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
4456  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
4457  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
4458  xmm6 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,k) * b1;
4459  xmm7 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,k) * b1;
4460  xmm8 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,k) * b1;
4461  }
4462 
4463  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 * factor );
4464  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 * factor );
4465  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 * factor );
4466  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 * factor );
4467  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, xmm5 * factor );
4468  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, j, xmm6 * factor );
4469  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*6UL, j, xmm7 * factor );
4470  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*7UL, j, xmm8 * factor );
4471  }
4472  }
4473  }
4474 
4475  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*4UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*5UL )
4476  {
4477  size_t j( 0UL );
4478 
4479  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
4480  {
4481  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4482  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4483  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
4484  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
4485  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
4486  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
4487  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
4488  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
4489  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
4490  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) : K ) );
4491 
4492  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8, xmm9, xmm10;
4493 
4494  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
4495  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
4496  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
4497  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
4498  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
4499  const SIMDType a5( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) );
4500  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
4501  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
4502  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
4503  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
4504  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
4505  xmm4 += a4 * b1;
4506  xmm5 += a5 * b1;
4507  xmm6 += a1 * b2;
4508  xmm7 += a2 * b2;
4509  xmm8 += a3 * b2;
4510  xmm9 += a4 * b2;
4511  xmm10 += a5 * b2;
4512  }
4513 
4514  (~C).store( i , j , xmm1 * factor );
4515  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , xmm2 * factor );
4516  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , xmm3 * factor );
4517  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j , xmm4 * factor );
4518  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j , xmm5 * factor );
4519  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, xmm6 * factor );
4520  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, xmm7 * factor );
4521  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, xmm8 * factor );
4522  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j+1UL, xmm9 * factor );
4523  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j+1UL, xmm10 * factor );
4524  }

4527  {
4528  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
4529  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
4530  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
4531  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
4532  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
4533  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) ):( K ) );
4534 
4535  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5;
4536

4538  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
4539  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
4540  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
4541  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
4542  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
4543  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
4544  }
4545 
4546  (~C).store( i , j, xmm1 * factor );
4547  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, xmm2 * factor );
4548  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, xmm3 * factor );
4549  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, xmm4 * factor );
4550  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, xmm5 * factor );

4807  :( K ) );

4825  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
4826  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
4827  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
4828 
4829  ElementType value = ElementType();
4830 
4831  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<K; ++k ) {
4832  value += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
4833  }
4834 
4835  (~C)(i,j) = value * scalar;
4836  }
4837  }
4838  }

4859  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
4860  selectLargeAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4861  {
4862  selectDefaultAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
4863  }

4917  //**BLAS-based assignment to dense matrices*****************************************************
4918 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
4919 
4932  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
4933  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
4934  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
4935  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
4936  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
4937  selectBlasAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
4938  {
4939  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
4940 
4941  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
4942  assign( C, B );
4943  trmm( C, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
4944  }
4945  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
4946  assign( C, A );
4947  trmm( C, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
4948  }
4949  else {
4950  gemm( C, A, B, ET(scalar), ET(0) );
4951  }
4952  }
4953 #endif

4955 
4956  //**Assignment to sparse matrices***************************************************************
4968  template< typename MT // Type of the target sparse matrix
4969  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target sparse matrix
4970  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
4971  assign( SparseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
4972  {
4973  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
4974 
4975  typedef IfTrue_< SO, ResultType, OppositeType > TmpType;
4976 
4977  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
4978  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
4979  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( ResultType );
4980  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType );
4981  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MATRICES_MUST_HAVE_SAME_STORAGE_ORDER( MT, TmpType );
4982  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_REFERENCE_TYPE( CompositeType_<TmpType> );
4983 
4984  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
4985  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
4986 
4987  const TmpType tmp( serial( rhs ) );
4988  assign( ~lhs, tmp );
4989  }
4990  //**********************************************************************************************
4991 
4992  //**Restructuring assignment to row-major matrices**********************************************
5006  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
5007  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
5008  assign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
5009  {
5010  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
5011 
5012  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
5013 
5014  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5015  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5016 
5017  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
5018  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
5019 
5020  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
5021  assign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
5022  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
5023  assign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * right * rhs.scalar_ );
5024  else
5025  assign( ~lhs, left * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
5026  }

5029  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices*******************************************************
5041  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
5042  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
5043  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
5044  addAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
5045  {
5046  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
5047 
5048  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5049  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5050 
5051  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
5052  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
5053 
5054  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || left.columns() == 0UL ) {
5055  return;
5056  }
5057 
5058  LT A( serial( left ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
5059  RT B( serial( right ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
5060 
5061  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5062  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
5063  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5064  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
5065  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5066  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5067 
5068  DMatScalarMultExpr::selectAddAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B, rhs.scalar_ );
5069  }

5071 
5072  //**Addition assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)************************************
5083  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5084  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5085  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5086  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5087  static inline void selectAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5088  {
5089  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value ) ||
5090  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
5091  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5092  else
5093  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5094  }

5097  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (general/general)*****************************
5111  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5112  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5113  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5114  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5115  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
5116  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5117  {
5118  const ResultType tmp( serial( A * B * scalar ) );
5119  addAssign( C, tmp );
5120  }

5122 
5123  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (general/diagonal)****************************
5137  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5138  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5139  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5140  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5141  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
5142  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5143  {
5144  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
5145 
5146  const size_t M( A.rows() );
5147  const size_t N( B.columns() );
5148 
5149  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
5150  {
5151  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5152  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j )
5153  :( 0UL ) );
5154  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5155  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL )
5156  :( M ) );
5157  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
5158 
5159  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
5160  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
5161 
5162  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
5163  C(i ,j) += A(i ,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
5164  C(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
5165  }
5166  if( ipos < iend ) {
5167  C(ipos,j) += A(ipos,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
5168  }
5169  }
5170  }
5171  //**********************************************************************************************
5172 
5173  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/general)****************************
5187  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5188  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5189  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5190  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5191  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
5192  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5193  {
5194  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
5195 
5196  const size_t M( A.rows() );
5197  const size_t N( B.columns() );
5198 
5199  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
5200  {
5201  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5202  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
5203  :( 0UL ) );
5204  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
5205  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
5206  :( M ) );
5207  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
5208 
5209  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
5210  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
5211 
5212  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
5213  C(i ,j) += A(i ,i ) * B(i ,j) * scalar;
5214  C(i+1UL,j) += A(i+1UL,i+1UL) * B(i+1UL,j) * scalar;
5215  }
5216  if( ipos < iend ) {
5217  C(ipos,j) += A(ipos,ipos) * B(ipos,j) * scalar;
5218  }
5219  }
5220  }
5221  //**********************************************************************************************
5222 
5223  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)***************************
5237  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5238  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5239  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5240  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5241  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
5242  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5243  {
5244  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
5245 
5246  for( size_t i=0UL; i<A.rows(); ++i ) {
5247  C(i,i) += A(i,i) * B(i,i) * scalar;
5248  }
5249  }

5266  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5267  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5268  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5269  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5270  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5271  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )

5276 
5277  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)*********
5292  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5293  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5294  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5295  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5296  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5297  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5298  {
5299  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT4 );
5300  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT5 );
5301  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT4> );
5302  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT5> );
5303 
5304  if( IsResizable<MT4>::value && !IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
5305  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
5306  addAssign( ~C, A * tmp * scalar );
5307  }
5308  else if( !IsResizable<MT4>::value && IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
5309  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
5310  addAssign( ~C, tmp * B * scalar );
5311  }
5312  else if( B.rows() * B.columns() <= A.rows() * A.columns() ) {
5313  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
5314  addAssign( ~C, A * tmp * scalar );
5315  }
5316  else {
5317  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
5318  addAssign( ~C, tmp * B * scalar );
5319  }
5320  }
5321  //**********************************************************************************************
5322 
5323  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)******
5338  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5339  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5340  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5341  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5342  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5343  selectSmallAddAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5344  {
5345  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT3>::value || !IsPadded<MT4>::value );
5346 
5347  const size_t M( A.rows() );
5348  const size_t N( B.columns() );
5349  const size_t K( A.columns() );
5350 
5351  const size_t ipos( remainder ? ( M & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : M );
5352  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( M - ( M % SIMDSIZE ) ) == ipos, "Invalid end calculation" );
5353 
5354  const SIMDType factor( set( scalar ) );
5355 
5356  size_t i( 0UL );
5357 
5358  if( IsIntegral_<ElementType> )
5359  {
5360  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*7UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*8UL ) {
5361  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
5362  {
5363  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5364  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5365  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5366  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5367  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
5368  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
5369  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5370  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
5371  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) )
5372  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K ) : K ) );
5373 
5374  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
5375 
5376  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
5377  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
5378  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
5379  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
5380  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
5381  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
5382  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
5383  xmm6 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,k) * b1;
5384  xmm7 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,k) * b1;
5385  xmm8 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,k) * b1;
5386  }
5387 
5388  (~C).store( i , j, (~C).load(i ,j) + xmm1 * factor );
5389  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) + xmm2 * factor );
5390  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) + xmm3 * factor );
5391  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) + xmm4 * factor );
5392  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j) + xmm5 * factor );
5393  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,j) + xmm6 * factor );
5394  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*6UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,j) + xmm7 * factor );
5395  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*7UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,j) + xmm8 * factor );
5396  }
5397  }
5398  }
5399 
5400  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*4UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*5UL )
5401  {
5402  size_t j( 0UL );
5403 
5404  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
5405  {
5406  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5407  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5408  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5409  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5410  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
5411  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
5412  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
5413  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
5414  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
5415  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) : K ) );
5416 
5417  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8, xmm9, xmm10;
5418 
5419  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
5420  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
5421  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
5422  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
5423  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
5424  const SIMDType a5( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) );
5425  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
5426  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
5427  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
5428  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
5429  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
5430  xmm4 += a4 * b1;
5431  xmm5 += a5 * b1;
5432  xmm6 += a1 * b2;
5433  xmm7 += a2 * b2;
5434  xmm8 += a3 * b2;
5435  xmm9 += a4 * b2;
5436  xmm10 += a5 * b2;
5437  }
5438 
5439  (~C).store( i , j , (~C).load(i ,j ) + xmm1 * factor );
5440  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j ) + xmm2 * factor );
5441  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j ) + xmm3 * factor );
5442  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j ) + xmm4 * factor );
5443  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j ) + xmm5 * factor );
5444  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, (~C).load(i ,j+1UL) + xmm6 * factor );
5445  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j+1UL) + xmm7 * factor );
5446  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j+1UL) + xmm8 * factor );
5447  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j+1UL) + xmm9 * factor );
5448  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j+1UL) + xmm10 * factor );
5449  }
5450 
5451  if( j < N )
5452  {
5453  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5454  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5455  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5456  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5457  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
5458  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) ):( K ) );

5460  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5;
5461

5463  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
5464  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
5465  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
5466  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
5467  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
5468  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
5469  }

5471  (~C).store( i , j, (~C).load(i ,j) + xmm1 * factor );
5472  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) + xmm2 * factor );
5473  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) + xmm3 * factor );
5474  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) + xmm4 * factor );
5475  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j) + xmm5 * factor );
5476  }

5486  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5487  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5488  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5489  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );

5491  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )

5493  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
5494  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K ) : K ) );

5499  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );

5506  xmm2 += a2 * b1;

5679  {
5680  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5681  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5682  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5683  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5684  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
5685  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )

5692  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
5693  xmm1 += a1 * set( B(k,j ) );
5694  xmm2 += a1 * set( B(k,j+1UL) );
5695  }
5696 
5697  (~C).store( i, j , (~C).load(i,j ) + xmm1 * factor );
5698  (~C).store( i, j+1UL, (~C).load(i,j+1UL) + xmm2 * factor );
5699  }
5700 
5701  if( j < N )
5702  {
5703  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5704  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5705  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5706  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5707  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
5708 
5709  SIMDType xmm1;
5710

5712  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * set( B(k,j) );
5713  }
5714 
5715  (~C).store( i, j, (~C).load(i,j) + xmm1 * factor );
5716  }
5717  }
5718 
5719  for( ; remainder && i<M; ++i )
5720  {
5721  size_t j( 0UL );

5723  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
5724  {
5725  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5726  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5727  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5728  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5729  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
5730  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
5731  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL )
5732  :( K ) );
5733 
5734  ElementType value1 = ElementType();
5735  ElementType value2 = ElementType();
5736 
5737  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
5738  value1 += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
5739  value2 += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
5740  }
5741 
5742  (~C)(i,j ) += value1 * scalar;
5743  (~C)(i,j+1UL) += value2 * scalar;
5744  }
5745 
5746  if( j < N )
5747  {
5748  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
5749  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
5750  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
5751  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
5752  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
5753 
5754  ElementType value = ElementType();
5755 
5756  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<K; ++k ) {
5757  value += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
5758  }
5759 
5760  (~C)(i,j) += value * scalar;
5761  }
5762  }
5763  }

5766  //**Default addition assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)******************************
5780  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5781  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5782  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5783  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5784  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5785  selectLargeAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5786  {
5787  selectDefaultAddAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5788  }
5789  //**********************************************************************************************
5790 
5791  //**Vectorized default addition assignment to dense matrices (large matrices)*******************
5806  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5807  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5808  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5809  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5810  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5811  selectLargeAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5812  {
5813  mmm( C, A, B, scalar, ST2(1) );
5814  }

5817  //**BLAS-based addition assignment to dense matrices (default)**********************************
5832  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5833  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5834  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5835  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5836  static inline DisableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5837  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5838  {
5839  selectLargeAddAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5840  }
5841  //**********************************************************************************************
5842 
5843  //**BLAS-based addition assignment to dense matrices********************************************
5844 #if BLAZE_BLAS_MODE && BLAZE_USE_BLAS_MATRIX_MATRIX_MULTIPLICATION
5845 
5858  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5859  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5860  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5861  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5862  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
5863  selectBlasAddAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5864  {
5865  typedef ElementType_<MT3> ET;
5866 
5867  if( IsTriangular<MT4>::value ) {
5868  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
5869  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
5870  addAssign( C, tmp );
5871  }
5872  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
5873  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
5874  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
5875  addAssign( C, tmp );
5876  }
5877  else {
5878  gemm( C, A, B, ET(scalar), ET(1) );
5879  }
5880  }
5881 #endif

5883 
5884  //**Restructuring addition assignment to row-major matrices*************************************
5899  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
5900  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
5901  addAssign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
5902  {
5903  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
5904 
5905  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
5906 
5907  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5908  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5909 
5910  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
5911  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
5912 
5913  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
5914  addAssign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
5915  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
5916  addAssign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * right * rhs.scalar_ );
5917  else
5918  addAssign( ~lhs, left * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
5919  }
5920  //**********************************************************************************************
5921 
5922  //**Addition assignment to sparse matrices******************************************************
5923  // No special implementation for the addition assignment to sparse matrices.
5924  //**********************************************************************************************
5925 
5926  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices****************************************************
5938  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
5939  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
5940  friend inline DisableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
5941  subAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
5942  {
5943  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
5944 
5945  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5946  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5947 
5948  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
5949  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
5950 
5951  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL || left.columns() == 0UL ) {
5952  return;
5953  }
5954 
5955  LT A( serial( left ) ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
5956  RT B( serial( right ) ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
5957 
5958  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5959  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
5960  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5961  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
5962  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
5963  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
5964 
5965  DMatScalarMultExpr::selectSubAssignKernel( ~lhs, A, B, rhs.scalar_ );
5966  }
5967  //**********************************************************************************************
5968 
5969  //**Subtraction assignment to dense matrices (kernel selection)*********************************
5980  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
5981  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
5982  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
5983  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
5984  static inline void selectSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
5985  {
5986  if( ( IsDiagonal<MT4>::value ) ||
5987  ( C.rows() * C.columns() < TDMATTDMATMULT_THRESHOLD ) )
5988  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5989  else
5990  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
5991  }
5992  //**********************************************************************************************
5993 
5994  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (general/general)**************************
6008  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6009  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6010  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6011  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6012  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
6013  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6014  {
6015  const ResultType tmp( serial( A * B * scalar ) );
6016  subAssign( C, tmp );
6017  }
6018  //**********************************************************************************************
6019 
6020  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (general/diagonal)*************************
6034  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6035  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6036  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6037  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6038  static inline EnableIf_< And< Not< IsDiagonal<MT4> >, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
6039  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6040  {
6041  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
6042 
6043  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6044  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6045 
6046  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
6047  {
6048  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6049  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT4>::value ? j+1UL : j )
6050  :( 0UL ) );
6051  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6052  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT4>::value ? j : j+1UL )
6053  :( M ) );
6054  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
6055 
6056  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
6057  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
6058 
6059  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
6060  C(i ,j) -= A(i ,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
6061  C(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
6062  }
6063  if( ipos < iend ) {
6064  C(ipos,j) -= A(ipos,j) * B(j,j) * scalar;
6065  }
6066  }
6067  }
6068  //**********************************************************************************************
6069 
6070  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/general)*************************
6084  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6085  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6086  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6087  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6088  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, Not< IsDiagonal<MT5> > > >
6089  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6090  {
6091  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
6092 
6093  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6094  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6095 
6096  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
6097  {
6098  const size_t ibegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6099  ?( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j )
6100  :( 0UL ) );
6101  const size_t iend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6102  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL )
6103  :( M ) );
6104  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( ibegin <= iend, "Invalid loop indices detected" );
6105 
6106  const size_t inum( iend - ibegin );
6107  const size_t ipos( ibegin + ( inum & size_t(-2) ) );
6108 
6109  for( size_t i=ibegin; i<ipos; i+=2UL ) {
6110  C(i ,j) -= A(i ,i ) * B(i ,j) * scalar;
6111  C(i+1UL,j) -= A(i+1UL,i+1UL) * B(i+1UL,j) * scalar;
6112  }
6113  if( ipos < iend ) {
6114  C(ipos,j) -= A(ipos,ipos) * B(ipos,j) * scalar;
6115  }
6116  }
6117  }
6118  //**********************************************************************************************
6119 
6120  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (diagonal/diagonal)************************
6134  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6135  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6136  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6137  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6138  static inline EnableIf_< And< IsDiagonal<MT4>, IsDiagonal<MT5> > >
6139  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6140  {
6141  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT3 );
6142 
6143  for( size_t i=0UL; i<A.rows(); ++i ) {
6144  C(i,i) -= A(i,i) * B(i,i) * scalar;
6145  }
6146  }

6149  //**Default subtraction assignment to dense matrices (small matrices)***************************
6163  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6164  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6165  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6166  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6167  static inline DisableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
6168  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6169  {
6170  selectDefaultSubAssignKernel( C, A, B, scalar );
6171  }

6173 
6174  //**Vectorized default subtraction assignment to row-major dense matrices (small matrices)******
6189  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6190  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6191  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6192  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6193  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
6194  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,false>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6195  {
6196  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT4 );
6197  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT5 );
6198  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT4> );
6199  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_ROW_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( OppositeType_<MT5> );
6200 
6201  if( IsResizable<MT4>::value && !IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
6202  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
6203  subAssign( ~C, A * tmp * scalar );
6204  }
6205  else if( !IsResizable<MT4>::value && IsResizable<MT5>::value ) {
6206  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
6207  subAssign( ~C, tmp * B * scalar );
6208  }
6209  else if( B.rows() * B.columns() <= A.rows() * A.columns() ) {
6210  const OppositeType_<MT5> tmp( serial( B ) );
6211  subAssign( ~C, A * tmp * scalar );
6212  }
6213  else {
6214  const OppositeType_<MT4> tmp( serial( A ) );
6215  subAssign( ~C, tmp * B * scalar );
6216  }
6217  }
6218  //**********************************************************************************************
6219 
6220  //**Vectorized default subtraction assignment to column-major dense matrices (small matrices)***
6235  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6236  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6237  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6238  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6239  static inline EnableIf_< UseVectorizedDefaultKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
6240  selectSmallSubAssignKernel( DenseMatrix<MT3,true>& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6241  {
6242  constexpr bool remainder( !IsPadded<MT3>::value || !IsPadded<MT4>::value );
6243 
6244  const size_t M( A.rows() );
6245  const size_t N( B.columns() );
6246  const size_t K( A.columns() );
6247 
6248  const size_t ipos( remainder ? ( M & size_t(-SIMDSIZE) ) : M );
6249  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( !remainder || ( M - ( M % SIMDSIZE ) ) == ipos, "Invalid end calculation" );
6250 
6251  const SIMDType factor( set( scalar ) );
6252 
6253  size_t i( 0UL );
6254 
6255  if( IsIntegral_<ElementType> )
6256  {
6257  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*7UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*8UL ) {
6258  for( size_t j=0UL; j<N; ++j )
6259  {
6260  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6261  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6262  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6263  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6264  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6265  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6266  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6267  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) ) )
6268  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j : j+1UL ) )
6269  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*8UL, K ) : K ) );
6270 
6271  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
6272 
6273  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6274  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
6275  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6276  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
6277  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
6278  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
6279  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
6280  xmm6 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,k) * b1;
6281  xmm7 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,k) * b1;
6282  xmm8 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,k) * b1;
6283  }
6284 
6285  (~C).store( i , j, (~C).load(i ,j) - xmm1 * factor );
6286  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) - xmm2 * factor );
6287  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) - xmm3 * factor );
6288  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) - xmm4 * factor );
6289  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j) - xmm5 * factor );
6290  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*5UL,j) - xmm6 * factor );
6291  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*6UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*6UL,j) - xmm7 * factor );
6292  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*7UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*7UL,j) - xmm8 * factor );
6293  }
6294  }
6295  }
6296 
6297  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*4UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*5UL )
6298  {
6299  size_t j( 0UL );
6300 
6301  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
6302  {
6303  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6304  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6305  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6306  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6307  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6308  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6309  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6310  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
6311  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
6312  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) : K ) );
6313 
6314  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8, xmm9, xmm10;
6315 
6316  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6317  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6318  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
6319  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
6320  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
6321  const SIMDType a5( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) );
6322  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
6323  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
6324  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6325  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
6326  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
6327  xmm4 += a4 * b1;
6328  xmm5 += a5 * b1;
6329  xmm6 += a1 * b2;
6330  xmm7 += a2 * b2;
6331  xmm8 += a3 * b2;
6332  xmm9 += a4 * b2;
6333  xmm10 += a5 * b2;
6334  }
6335 
6336  (~C).store( i , j , (~C).load(i ,j ) - xmm1 * factor );
6337  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j ) - xmm2 * factor );
6338  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j ) - xmm3 * factor );
6339  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j ) - xmm4 * factor );
6340  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j ) - xmm5 * factor );
6341  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, (~C).load(i ,j+1UL) - xmm6 * factor );
6342  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j+1UL) - xmm7 * factor );
6343  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j+1UL) - xmm8 * factor );
6344  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j+1UL) - xmm9 * factor );
6345  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j+1UL) - xmm10 * factor );
6346  }
6347 
6348  if( j < N )
6349  {
6350  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6351  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6352  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6353  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6354  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6355  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*5UL, K ) ):( K ) );
6356 
6357  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5;
6358 
6359  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6360  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
6361  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6362  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
6363  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
6364  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
6365  xmm5 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,k) * b1;
6366  }
6367 
6368  (~C).store( i , j, (~C).load(i ,j) - xmm1 * factor );
6369  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) - xmm2 * factor );
6370  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) - xmm3 * factor );
6371  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) - xmm4 * factor );
6372  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*4UL,j) - xmm5 * factor );
6373  }
6374  }
6375 
6376  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*3UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*4UL )
6377  {
6378  size_t j( 0UL );
6379 
6380  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
6381  {
6382  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6383  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6384  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6385  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6386  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6387  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6388  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6389  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
6390  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
6391  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K ) : K ) );
6392 
6393  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6, xmm7, xmm8;
6394 
6395  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6396  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6397  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
6398  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
6399  const SIMDType a4( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) );
6400  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
6401  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
6402  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6403  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
6404  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
6405  xmm4 += a4 * b1;
6406  xmm5 += a1 * b2;
6407  xmm6 += a2 * b2;
6408  xmm7 += a3 * b2;
6409  xmm8 += a4 * b2;
6410  }
6411 
6412  (~C).store( i , j , (~C).load(i ,j ) - xmm1 * factor );
6413  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j ) - xmm2 * factor );
6414  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j ) - xmm3 * factor );
6415  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j ) - xmm4 * factor );
6416  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, (~C).load(i ,j+1UL) - xmm5 * factor );
6417  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j+1UL) - xmm6 * factor );
6418  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j+1UL) - xmm7 * factor );
6419  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j+1UL) - xmm8 * factor );
6420  }
6421 
6422  if( j < N )
6423  {
6424  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6425  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6426  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6427  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6428  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6429  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*4UL, K ) ):( K ) );
6430 
6431  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
6432 
6433  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6434  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
6435  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6436  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
6437  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
6438  xmm4 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,k) * b1;
6439  }
6440 
6441  (~C).store( i , j, (~C).load(i ,j) - xmm1 * factor );
6442  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) - xmm2 * factor );
6443  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) - xmm3 * factor );
6444  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*3UL,j) - xmm4 * factor );

6447 
6448  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE*2UL) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*3UL )
6449  {
6450  size_t j( 0UL );
6451 
6452  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
6453  {
6454  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6455  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6456  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6457  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6458  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6459  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6460  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6461  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
6462  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
6463  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, K ) : K ) );
6464 
6465  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4, xmm5, xmm6;
6466 
6467  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6468  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6469  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) );
6470  const SIMDType a3( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) );
6471  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
6472  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
6473  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6474  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
6475  xmm3 += a3 * b1;
6476  xmm4 += a1 * b2;
6477  xmm5 += a2 * b2;
6478  xmm6 += a3 * b2;
6479  }
6480 
6481  (~C).store( i , j , (~C).load(i ,j ) - xmm1 * factor );
6482  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j ) - xmm2 * factor );
6483  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j ) - xmm3 * factor );
6484  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, (~C).load(i ,j+1UL) - xmm4 * factor );
6485  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j+1UL) - xmm5 * factor );
6486  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j+1UL) - xmm6 * factor );
6487  }
6488 
6489  if( j < N )
6490  {
6491  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6492  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6493  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6494  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6495  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6496  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*3UL, K ) ):( K ) );
6497 
6498  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3;
6499 
6500  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6501  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
6502  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6503  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE ,k) * b1;
6504  xmm3 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,k) * b1;
6505  }
6506 
6507  (~C).store( i , j, (~C).load(i ,j) - xmm1 * factor );
6508  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE , j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE ,j) - xmm2 * factor );
6509  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE*2UL,j) - xmm3 * factor );
6510  }
6511  }
6512 
6513  for( ; (i+SIMDSIZE) < ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE*2UL )
6514  {
6515  size_t j( 0UL );
6516 
6517  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
6518  {
6519  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6520  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6521  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6522  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6523  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6524  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6525  ?( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )
6526  ?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, K, ( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) ) )
6527  :( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL ) )
6528  :( IsLower<MT4>::value ? min( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, K ) : K ) );
6529 
6530  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2, xmm3, xmm4;
6531 
6532  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6533  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i ,k) );
6534  const SIMDType a2( A.load(i+SIMDSIZE,k) );
6535  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j ) ) );
6536  const SIMDType b2( set( B(k,j+1UL) ) );
6537  xmm1 += a1 * b1;
6538  xmm2 += a2 * b1;
6539  xmm3 += a1 * b2;
6540  xmm4 += a2 * b2;
6541  }
6542 
6543  (~C).store( i , j , (~C).load(i ,j ) - xmm1 * factor );
6544  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE, j , (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE,j ) - xmm2 * factor );
6545  (~C).store( i , j+1UL, (~C).load(i ,j+1UL) - xmm3 * factor );
6546  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE, j+1UL, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE,j+1UL) - xmm4 * factor );
6547  }
6548 
6549  if( j < N )
6550  {
6551  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6552  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6553  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6554  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6555  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6556  const size_t kend( ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( min( i+SIMDSIZE*2UL, K ) ):( K ) );
6557 
6558  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
6559 
6560  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6561  const SIMDType b1( set( B(k,j) ) );
6562  xmm1 += A.load(i ,k) * b1;
6563  xmm2 += A.load(i+SIMDSIZE,k) * b1;
6564  }
6565 
6566  (~C).store( i , j, (~C).load(i ,j) - xmm1 * factor );
6567  (~C).store( i+SIMDSIZE, j, (~C).load(i+SIMDSIZE,j) - xmm2 * factor );
6568  }
6569  }
6570 
6571  for( ; i<ipos; i+=SIMDSIZE )
6572  {
6573  size_t j( 0UL );
6574 
6575  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
6576  {
6577  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6578  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6579  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6580  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6581  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6582  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6583  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL )
6584  :( K ) );
6585 
6586  SIMDType xmm1, xmm2;
6587 
6588  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6589  const SIMDType a1( A.load(i,k) );
6590  xmm1 += a1 * set( B(k,j ) );
6591  xmm2 += a1 * set( B(k,j+1UL) );
6592  }
6593 
6594  (~C).store( i, j , (~C).load(i,j ) - xmm1 * factor );
6595  (~C).store( i, j+1UL, (~C).load(i,j+1UL) - xmm2 * factor );
6596  }
6597 
6598  if( j < N )
6599  {
6600  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6601  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6602  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6603  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6604  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6605 
6606  SIMDType xmm1;
6607 
6608  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<K; ++k ) {
6609  xmm1 += A.load(i,k) * set( B(k,j) );
6610  }
6611 
6612  (~C).store( i, j, (~C).load(i,j) - xmm1 * factor );
6613  }
6614  }
6615 
6616  for( ; remainder && i<M; ++i )
6617  {
6618  size_t j( 0UL );
6619 
6620  for( ; (j+2UL) <= N; j+=2UL )
6621  {
6622  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6623  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6624  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6625  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6626  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6627  const size_t kend( ( IsUpper<MT5>::value )
6628  ?( IsStrictlyUpper<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j+2UL )
6629  :( K ) );
6630 
6631  ElementType value1 = ElementType();
6632  ElementType value2 = ElementType();
6633 
6634  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<kend; ++k ) {
6635  value1 += A(i,k) * B(k,j );
6636  value2 += A(i,k) * B(k,j+1UL);
6637  }
6638 
6639  (~C)(i,j ) -= value1 * scalar;
6640  (~C)(i,j+1UL) -= value2 * scalar;
6641  }
6642 
6643  if( j < N )
6644  {
6645  const size_t kbegin( ( IsLower<MT5>::value )
6646  ?( ( IsUpper<MT4>::value )
6647  ?( max( i, ( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) ) )
6648  :( IsStrictlyLower<MT5>::value ? j+1UL : j ) )
6649  :( IsUpper<MT4>::value ? i : 0UL ) );
6650 
6651  ElementType value = ElementType();
6652 
6653  for( size_t k=kbegin; k<K; ++k ) {
6654  value += A(i,k) * B(k,j);
6655  }
6656 
6657  (~C)(i,j) -= value * scalar;
6658  }
6659  }
6660  }

6742 
6755  template< typename MT3 // Type of the left-hand side target matrix
6756  , typename MT4 // Type of the left-hand side matrix operand
6757  , typename MT5 // Type of the right-hand side matrix operand
6758  , typename ST2 > // Type of the scalar value
6759  static inline EnableIf_< UseBlasKernel<MT3,MT4,MT5,ST2> >
6760  selectBlasSubAssignKernel( MT3& C, const MT4& A, const MT5& B, ST2 scalar )
6761  {

6763

6765  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( B ) );
6766  trmm( tmp, A, CblasLeft, ( IsLower<MT4>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
6767  subAssign( C, tmp );
6768  }
6769  else if( IsTriangular<MT5>::value ) {
6770  ResultType_<MT3> tmp( serial( A ) );
6771  trmm( tmp, B, CblasRight, ( IsLower<MT5>::value )?( CblasLower ):( CblasUpper ), ET(scalar) );
6772  subAssign( C, tmp );
6773  }
6774  else {
6775  gemm( C, A, B, ET(-scalar), ET(1) );
6776  }
6777  }
6778 #endif

6795  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
6796  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
6797  subAssign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
6798  {
6799  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
6800 
6801  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
6802 
6803  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6804  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
6805 
6806  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
6807  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
6808 
6809  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
6810  subAssign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
6811  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
6812  subAssign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * right * rhs.scalar_ );
6813  else
6814  subAssign( ~lhs, left * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
6815  }

6830  //**SMP assignment to dense matrices************************************************************
6845  template< typename MT // Type of the target dense matrix
6846  , bool SO > // Storage order of the target dense matrix
6847  friend inline EnableIf_< IsEvaluationRequired<MT,MT1,MT2> >
6848  smpAssign( DenseMatrix<MT,SO>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
6849  {
6850  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
6851 
6852  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6853  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
6854 
6855  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
6856  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
6857 
6858  if( (~lhs).rows() == 0UL || (~lhs).columns() == 0UL ) {
6859  return;
6860  }
6861  else if( left.columns() == 0UL ) {
6862  reset( ~lhs );
6863  return;
6864  }
6865 
6866  LT A( left ); // Evaluation of the left-hand side dense matrix operand
6867  RT B( right ); // Evaluation of the right-hand side dense matrix operand
6868 
6869  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == left.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6870  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.columns() == left.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
6871  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.rows() == right.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6872  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == right.columns() , "Invalid number of columns" );
6873  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( A.rows() == (~lhs).rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
6874  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( B.columns() == (~lhs).columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
6875 
6876  smpAssign( ~lhs, A * B * rhs.scalar_ );
6877  }

7090  //**Restructuring SMP subtraction assignment to row-major matrices******************************
7105  template< typename MT > // Type of the target matrix
7106  friend inline EnableIf_< CanExploitSymmetry<MT,MT1,MT2> >
7107  smpSubAssign( Matrix<MT,false>& lhs, const DMatScalarMultExpr& rhs )
7108  {
7109  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
7110 
7111  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_NOT_BE_SYMMETRIC_MATRIX_TYPE( MT );
7112 
7113  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).rows() == rhs.rows() , "Invalid number of rows" );
7114  BLAZE_INTERNAL_ASSERT( (~lhs).columns() == rhs.columns(), "Invalid number of columns" );
7115 
7116  LeftOperand_<MMM> left ( rhs.matrix_.leftOperand() );
7117  RightOperand_<MMM> right( rhs.matrix_.rightOperand() );
7118 
7119  if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value && IsSymmetric<MT2>::value )
7120  smpSubAssign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
7121  else if( IsSymmetric<MT1>::value )
7122  smpSubAssign( ~lhs, trans( left ) * right * rhs.scalar_ );
7123  else
7124  smpSubAssign( ~lhs, left * trans( right ) * rhs.scalar_ );
7125  }
7126  //**********************************************************************************************
7127 
7128  //**SMP subtraction assignment to sparse matrices***********************************************
7129  // No special implementation for the SMP subtraction assignment to sparse matrices.
7130  //**********************************************************************************************
7131 
7132  //**SMP multiplication assignment to dense matrices*********************************************
7133  // No special implementation for the SMP multiplication assignment to dense matrices.
7134  //**********************************************************************************************
7135 
7136  //**SMP multiplication assignment to sparse matrices********************************************
7137  // No special implementation for the SMP multiplication assignment to sparse matrices.
7138  //**********************************************************************************************
7139 
7140  //**Compile time checks*************************************************************************
7141  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MMM );
7142  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MMM );
7143  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MT1 );
7144  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT1 );
7145  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_DENSE_MATRIX_TYPE( MT2 );
7146  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_COLUMN_MAJOR_MATRIX_TYPE( MT2 );
7147  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_NUMERIC_TYPE( ST );
7148  BLAZE_CONSTRAINT_MUST_BE_SAME_TYPE( ST, RightOperand );
7149  //**********************************************************************************************
7150 };
7152 //*************************************************************************************************
7153 
7154 
7155 
7156 
7157 //=================================================================================================
7158 //
7159 // GLOBAL BINARY ARITHMETIC OPERATORS
7160 //
7161 //=================================================================================================
7162 
7163 //*************************************************************************************************
7189 template< typename T1 // Type of the left-hand side dense matrix
7190  , typename T2 > // Type of the right-hand side dense matrix
7191 inline const TDMatTDMatMultExpr<T1,T2>
7192  operator*( const DenseMatrix<T1,true>& lhs, const DenseMatrix<T2,true>& rhs )
7193 {
7194  BLAZE_FUNCTION_TRACE;
7195 
7196  if( (~lhs).columns() != (~rhs).rows() ) {
7197  BLAZE_THROW_INVALID_ARGUMENT( "Matrix sizes do not match" );
7198  }
7199 
7200  return TDMatTDMatMultExpr<T1,T2>( ~lhs, ~rhs );
7201 }

blaze::TDMatSVecMultExprTrait
Evaluation of the expression type of a transpose dense matrix/sparse vector multiplication.Via this type trait it is possible to evaluate the resulting expression type of a transpose dense matrix/sparse vector multiplication. Given the column-major dense matrix type MT and the non-transpose sparse vector type VT, the nested type Type corresponds to the resulting expression type. In case either MT is not a column-major dense matrix type or VT is not a non-transpose sparse vector type, the resulting data type Type is set to INVALID_TYPE.

Evaluation of the expression type of a dense vector/transpose dense matrix multiplication.Via this type trait it is possible to evaluate the resulting expression type of a dense vector/transpose dense matrix multiplication.
